<br>
but my question is: i am lvl 10 now, and haven't been working on my 1hb at all (it's at 0).  should i be working on that along with my h2h?...i also dont know what the best way to raise it would be.  would i get a skill increase slaughtering those decayed skellies or do i have to actually try against monsters more my level? sry if this has been answered...but i couldnt find it anywhere in the guides or anything. thanks in advance <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ubontonsilentfist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bonton Silent Fist</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 17<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/3/02 10:39:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1848.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: new to melee and need some advice on skills</span><hr size=1> First of all to get a skill up the mob has to give XP.  Dont know how your funds are but a Black jack can be had pretty cheap these days.  I would suggest putting in in the off hand and just work on lvling - the skill will catch up in time.<br>
 <p>Bonton<BR>
The One Eyed Monk<BR>
"Shaken not stirred"<BR>
60th lvl Grandmaster<BR>
Fennin Ro<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/udakkin2.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dakkin2</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 27<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/6/02 1:35:45 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1848.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: new to melee and need some advice on skills</span><hr size=1> Yes you should work on 1Hb if you possibly can, but...<br>
<br>
I'm guessing you're not in a position to buy a neat 1Hb or get to Maidens Eye and ooc for someone to tell you when they have one of those nodrop Goranga Spiked Clubs about to rot, so for a little while at least you're probably doing more damage with hand to hand than you could with the 1Hbs you can afford.<br>
<br>
Once you get a few more levels it's easy to raise a weapon skill from zero to maxed anyway, by finding a good group killing mobs that con blue to you, and asking them if you can hit their mobs to skill up for a few hours.<br>
<br>
Good luck though - it must be insanely difficult starting from scratch these days when everyone else is running around in gear bought by their level 60 main characters.  I hope everything goes well, and it's still possible for you to have fun.<br>
<br>
Dak <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/udakkin2.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dakkin2</A> at: 9/6/02 1:37:03 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukorlik.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Korlik</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 49<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/8/02 7:13:55 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1848.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: new to melee and need some advice on skills</span><hr size=1> You should work on all your weapon skills, you will want them maxed at high level, and doing it then takes up extra time and lowers DPS. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=181185">Korlik Klawfist</a><BR>
Grandmaster of Luclin
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ucenkala.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cenkala</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/9/02 10:37:54 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1848.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: new to melee and need some advice on skills</span><hr size=1> Essence of Dol is a great 1hb to 10/28 +5str - bought one for 15pp in the Bazaar. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=124125 ><b>Baroness Cenkala Sokokar - Iksar Oracle </b></a>
<br><br><b>Sacrament of Chaos</b><br><br>

</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uanarkhan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>anarkhan</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Anarcho-Monk</span><br>  Posts: 353<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/12/02 3:19:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1848.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> mad skill</span><hr size=1> Practice &quot;strafing&quot; on mobs.<br>
<br>
Using the arrow keys on your keyboard, you can learn to make perfect circles around an opponent instinctively. You need to practice until it becomes second nature. <br>
<br>
This is done by hitting the left (or left)-arrow and up-arrow keys at the same time that you're holding down the control key; letting off those keys and momentarily hitting the right (or left)-arrow key to keep the target in front of you.<br>
<br>
This skill can come in handy in situations where you want to, or are forced into, PvP. It's also good for when you want to spot a mob in a particular place or position <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ufingalpeacebringer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fingal Peacebringer</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.greenmansgrove.org/pics/purpdrag1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk</span><br>  Posts: 124<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/14/02 9:44:47 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1848.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.enteract.com/~middltn/grnman.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: mad skill</span><hr size=1> IF you're worried about skilling up quickly, I would suggest either an Essence of Dol or a Fighting Baton, either of which should be available very cheaply in the Bazaar. While the Essence of Dol does more damage, the fighting baton is nearly 33% faster than the EoD (10/28 vs 8/20), so if you're looking to skill up quickly, you might lean towards the Fighting Baton. As well, either of these weapons will serve you well as a good weapon into your 40's or so, since they end up with a better damage delay ratio than your fists until then. You might even think about getting 2 batons or a baton and an EoD once you have brought your skill up, since it will significantly increase your damage output until the 40's.<br>
<br>
Also remember to skill up your 2hb skill. This can be done very easily for cheap with a Bamboo Bo stick, which used to run about 100-200 plat. I haven't seen the prices on them since the Bazaar opened up, but they probably are either the same or less expensive. This is a good weapon to use in your low leves, since it's going to be doing more than your hands do right now, but remember that you're going to want to upgrade fairly soon, since you will do more damage with other weapons than with your Bamboo Bo fairly quickly. It's primary use will be to bring up your skill quickly. The other weapon you might look for is an Adamantite Bo, which is a great damage delay weapon, but become less useful when you hit 30th level, and it starts to proc an AoE attack.<br>
<br>
Good luck!<br>
 <p>Fingal PeaceBringer </br>
Master of the 57th Season, Cazic-Thule Server</br>
<img src=http://www.greenmansgrove.org/pics/purpdrag1.GIF></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukorph.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Korph</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/14/02 12:06:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1848.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: mad skill</span><hr size=1> Pick up a fast 1hb in the bazaar if you have the cash.  One of the cheapest fast 1hb weapons around is the Fighting Baton.<br>
<br>
When I first started Korph I had an ubertwink friend (was using a jade mace!!!) and he gave me a Cane of the Tranquil, which I weilded in my main hand and fist in my offhand until about level 30 (at which point I transferred money from all my characters and bought a Jade Mace for myself, meh!).<br>
<br>
I'd try to get a fighting baton and use it in your main hand, fist in offhand.  That way your skills will remain up (my H2H wasn't maxed, but was nearly so).<br>
<br>
By the way, I am now 51 and using an IFS (sold the Jade Mace and Cane of the Tranquil, meh!) and kicking ass!<br>
<br>
It was funny when I was in KC and won the roll on a Jade Mace a few weeks back... lent it to a friend. <p>-Korph
